      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW QATAR (1) skirted wide from an outside draw last start and found the front, leading throughout to win (22.88) at Warragul in a Grade 5 over 400m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from five starts. Can continue the winning form. DR. XANTHIC (6) missed the frame last time when fifth (24.85) at this track in a Grade 5 but not beaten far the start prior. Expected to bounce back to best. CROSS LOCKS (2) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fifth wasn't far away finishing 2.75 lengths from the winner (26.20). Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. DR. ODIN (4) is another with top-three prospects.",
